	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=560><span id= >Milquetoast</span></a><br><span id=notbold>10 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I always cast damage shield on my tanks when group unless they are a monk or rogue :) It's an effective spell that helps guarentee the mob will stick on the tank and not the blasters if they do not over nuke.&nbsp;&nbsp;We were taking on red creatures with minimal deaths by having the attention of the mob stay where it should....on the tanks. The other spell that I throw on any mob right away is snare.  A runner can mean certain death in several situations.  Snare also means that the battle will only go until the creature begins the walk.  After that it becomes a beat on the monster until it's dead.  Mobs won't even defend themselves once they start the walk.  If they are rooted however, they will defend themselves.</p>&nbsp;<br>Milquetoast Outland<br>Druid of Tunare-Karana</td></td></tr>
