	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=8&mid=96686895023306>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96686895023306>Damage shield advice</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=96686895023306#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 10:42 AM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=650><span id= >Tutten</span></a><br><span id=notbold>14 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I use damage shields frequently.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's never resisted, and so is about the most mana efficient spell to use against a red mob.<br><br>Having a damage shield on does not add to the aggro list of the mob.  If a mob is killed by damage from the damage shield, with no other damage done, the mob will disappear without leaving a corpse or giving experience.  (Try buffing a level 1 with a high damage shield and have an orc pawn hit them).<br><br>Casting a damage shield on a player that is engaged with mobs does increase the mob's hate for you, however.  In my usual group, we have a ranger pulling and a warrior waiting with the group.  When the ranger calls inc, I stand up and shield the warrior.  When the ranger arrives with the mob, I'll shield him, too, then cast a DoT.  With two taunting tanks, the mobs only rarely aggro on me.<br><br>DON'T DAMAGE SHIELD MONKS OR ROGUES!  A bit of advice I've gotten from monks is that having a damage shield can cost them heavily.  If they're getting beat up to the point where they need to feign death, a mob often gets one swing in even after a successful feign.  If they hit and take damage from a damage shield, they will disbelieve the feign death.<br><br>Casting heal on a monk that has feigned death will also break a mob's belief in the monk's death - so you'd better be able to keep the monk alive if you do it!<br><br>I would avoid using a damage shield on a rogue, also.  First, it's generally a waste of mana, since a good rogue avoids getting hit at all.  Second, it may interfere with their ability to evade.<br><br>When grouping with an enchanter, I find damage shields much less useful.  Either they're slowing the mob attack to practically nothing, or stunning/mezzing everything, or we're fear kiting a big heavy hitter.  If your tanks aren't getting hit, damage shields don't do any good.  It's good to group with enchanters...<br></p>&nbsp;<br>tuttenclawstorm@yahoo.com<br></td></td></tr>
