	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Agreed, as almost every druid or ranger knows - snare everything.&nbsp;&nbsp;But the most important thing I think most druids need to know is that Shield of Thorn seires of spells will outdamage what you can do with whatever weapon of yours you have.  ALWAYS CAST IT and then, personally, I chose to sit.  Then I snare when the mob is at about 50%.<br><br>Also, the group thorns is nice at higher level, at 1st, I thought, wow - useless, cost more then 2x as much and dosen't do as much damage, but I now use it all the time cause it saves time.  I rather cast it even if I only have one tank in the group - cause rarly is he the only one hit.  Also, one cast and sit means more time to med.<br><br>Another thought - when grouping with enchanters - just put the Dots away - except for maybe 1, just incase.  Let the Enchanter do his thing - remeber - you can't mez (and have it stick) a Dot'd mob.<br><br>After level 25 or so, don't even try to melee, it is a waste.  The only time I now melee (lvl 55) is when I am solo, oom, and I have a mob snared and running - then i just beat on it till it dies, tho usually, i just sit, med for 30 or so seconds - then nuke it.<br><br>Remember, Druids are casters, the weakest of the priest class, our AC blows (cause Verant thinks that Druid armor should be heavy and worthless) so med when you can, mana is life.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
