	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;Hmmm...yet I can still wade into combat and solo high blues at 45 (the right blues, that is...no way I'm tanking an HG, sorry...) :)<br>  I WANT my AC to suck a little...but the damage I take to be minimal.  My AGI is high so that I (hopefully) take less damage per blow as ds damage is piling onto the mob.<br>  And yes, that's right, when I solo unless I'm kiting I don't use my Paw...I use a Wraithbone Hammer.<br>  As for group thorns, unless you're in a really tank-heavy group or one that doesn't know what they're doing, there should be little need for it.  No one but tanks generally needs ds, if those tanks are competent.  You do better damage, spend less mana, and get a longer duration with the individual ds's.<br>  So while you're sitting on your butt medding extra, my individual ds's are up and I have a little more mana for that one extra heal or evac I may need during combat.<br>   There are exceptions to this...when you have 4 or 5 tanks in your group...but those are pretty rare occurrences.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
