	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I disagree partially with the melee part... 20 or so damage here and there can add up.. just make sure you are not the one taking the hits.&nbsp;&nbsp;In smaller groups, without a cleric this changes since your mana is more important.  In larger groups or ones with clerics it doesn't hurt to help out instead of mana burning.. hold on to it.  In a group situation I feel the druid is more of the what if this happens member.  We don't add all that much to the group as a primary member but we excel at saving the day when others are unable to help.  Examples of this is healing the cleric when they are hurting, taking the mob off the cleric, finishing that mob before he gets more friends, evac of course, an extra rooter/snarer, back up heals for tanks you get the idea.<br><br>In regards to the thorn tech, another thing I have found is to cast the thorns (group or otherwise) before the puller pulls. This keeps the agro down and gives you a bit more time to regain that mana.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
